<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_2_3_4">
   <title>Report Viewing Features</title>
   <conbody>
    <p>The dashboard report viewing is nearly the same as the viewing features used to view reports
      accessed through the Data Design menu. For details on viewing reports, see <xref
        href="c_sen_anal-3_1-Viewing-Reports_crm.xml"/>. When accessed, the Dashboard always
      displays the most recent run of the report.</p>
    <fig><title>Figure 1-12: Dashboard Report Viewing</title><image href="./media/Image_040.png" placement="break" scale="45"/></fig>
     <p>Hover over the dashboard pod, you want to display the report chart, the toggle menu <image
       href="media/toggle_menu_dashboard.png" placement="inline"/> pops up. Choose the middle button <image
         href="media/toggle_menu_dashboard._middle.png" placement="inline"/>
       to toggle the grid off and maximize the chart.</p>
    <fig>
      <title>Figure 1-13: Maximizing Chart for Viewing with Toggle Grid Display</title>
      <image href="./media/Image_041.png" placement="break" scale="50"/>
    </fig>
     <p>Choose the bottom button <image
       href="media/toggle_menu_dashboard._bottom.png" placement="inline"/>
       to toggle the chart off and maximize the grid.</p>
     <fig>
       <title>Figure 1-13: Maximizing Chart for Viewing with Toggle Grid Display</title>
       <image href="./media/Image_041_1.png" placement="break" scale="50"/>
     </fig>
  </conbody>
</concept>
